1. Nf3 {The Reti Opening.A flexible move that does not commit the pawn structure to adopt. White can play 
2.d4 or 2.e4 or even 2.c4 depending up Black's response} 1...d6 {White's first move prevented Black from playing 1...e5
So Black prepares to play ...e5 later by this pawn move.}
2. g3 {White decides to fianchetto his light-squared bishop to g2 and control the h1-a8 diagonal.The downside of this move is that 
if White were to play O-O later and the bishop on g2 were to get exchanged then the light squares f3,g2 and h3 in front of the 
king would become weak.}
2...e5 {Black plays according to the plan on move 1 and controls the dark square in the centre d4}
3. Bg2 {White's bishop will exert pressure on the light squares e4 and d5 in the centre and White is using pieces to stake equal claim in the centre}
3...f5 {Another pawn move by Black, this time controlling the e4 square.Black is trying to combat the light square control by White}
4. c4 {White is now controlling the d5 square.White has not only developed his kingside pieces but also staking claim on the central light squares}
4...Nf6 {Black no only develops a piece but also counters White's aim to control the d5 square}
5. b4 !? {An interesting move that declares White's intention to expand on the queenside.This move also allows White to 
fianchetto the dark-squared bishop to b2. This saves White future tempi of playing a3 or c3 to play b4.Another good response would have been 5.Nc3}  
5...e4 ?! {Black expands further in the centre and nullifies White's influence on the h1-a8 diagonal.
This move was not necessary as Black played the first two moves to occupy e5 and now has given up that achievement to give White's knight 
a kick}
6. Nd4 {White keeps his knight on the central square}
6...d5 {Black now solidifies his hold on the light square e4 but has made too many pawn moves}
7. cxd5 {White is ahead in development and now exchanges the flank c-pawn for the central pawn on d5}
7...Nxd5 {Black captured with the intention of attacking the b4 pawn twice. Also possible was 7...Qxd5
}
